@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Hiking & Photography";
}

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <title>@ViewData["Title"]</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="~/css/site.css"> <!-- Link to your CSS -->
</head>
<body>
<header class="page-header">
    <h1>Welcome to my landscape photography page!</h1>
</header>

<section class="content">
    <!-- These are the two images and am adding to the homepage of my website--> 
    <img class="image" src="~/images/hiking.jpg" alt="Hiking Adventure" width="400">
    <img class="image" src="~/images/landscape.jpg" alt="Landscape Photography" width="400">


    <!-- This is my paragaphs explaining my hobby -->
    <p>
        There’s something incredible about stepping onto a trail, camera in hand, and knowing that I’m about to capture a moment that no one else will ever see exactly the same way.
        Hiking and landscape photography go hand in hand for me—one fuels the other.
        I love the challenge of reaching those breathtaking viewpoints, waiting for the perfect light, and snapping a shot that captures not just the scene but the feeling of being there.
    </p>
    <p>
        I’ve always been drawn to the beauty of the outdoors, whether it’s a misty mountain morning, the sun dipping below a rugged canyon, or the endless blues of the ocean stretching to the horizon.
        Hiking has taken me to some unforgettable places, and photography is my way of preserving those moments.
        There’s something rewarding about getting that one perfect shot after a long climb—especially knowing that I earned the view.
        It’s not just about taking photos; it’s about experiencing nature, appreciating the details, and sharing the beauty with others.
    </p>
</section>

<footer class="footer">
    <a class="button-link" href="@Url.Action("Calculator", "Home")">Go to Calculator</a>
</footer>
</body>
</html>